claim.claim-text:
1. A fiber optic trunk cable, comprising:
a plurality of optical fibers;
first and second terminals attached to opposite ends of the fibers, each of the terminals having an alignment key;
wherein the fibers enter the first terminal in an arrangement of 2N rows, wherein N is an integer;
wherein the fibers enter the second terminal in an arrangement of 2N rows;
each fiber defining a position in the first terminal with respect to the alignment key that is laterally transposed and row-inverted to the position the fiber defines in the second terminal.

4. A fiber optic system, comprising:
first and second fan-outs comprising, respectively, first and second transceiver-side mating terminals, the first fan-out further comprising a first plurality of optical fibers attached to the first transceiver-side terminal(s), the second fan-out comprising a second plurality of optical fibers attached to the second transceiver-side terminal(s), the first and second fan-outs further comprising first and second trunk cable-mating terminals; and
a trunk cable comprising:
a third plurality of optical fibers;
first and second trunk cable terminals attached to opposite ends of the third plurality of fibers, each of the first and second trunk cable terminals having an alignment key;
wherein the third fibers enter the first trunk cable terminal in an arrangement of 2N rows, wherein N is an integer;
wherein the third fibers enter the second trunk cable terminal in an arrangement of 2N rows;
each third fiber defining a position in the first trunk cable terminal with respect to the alignment key that is laterally transposed and row-inverted (relative to a line parallel to and bisecting the rows) to the position the third fiber defines in the second trunk cable terminal;
wherein the first trunk cable terminal is connected with the first trunk cable-mating terminal, and wherein the second trunk cable terminal is connected with the second trunk cable-mating terminal, each connection mated with an adapter having aligned keyways.
